            <title>[CAMEL-18377] camel-jpa producer does not reuse existing EntityManager in transaction and create its own one</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18377</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;camel-jpa producer does not reuse  the existing EntityManager in transaction and create its own one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens when JpaTransactionManager is used. It creates an EntityManager for transactions in the doBegin() method.&lt;br/&gt;
So there will be two EntityManagers and two connections even if there is only one route for the jpa producer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
